The 2022 ABC Motsepe national playoffs will be held in Potchefstroom from June 14-19 after the SA Football Association conducted the round fixture at the Safa House on Monday. Two finalists at the tournament will get a chance to gain automatic promotion to the Glad Africa Championship for the 2022/23 season. “Three groups of stages are scheduled for 13-16 June 2022 at the North West University in the Potchefstroom campus,” said Safa, adding that the semi-finals will take place on Friday, June 17 at Olen Park Stadium, with the final taking place at the same venue on June 19. Safa said the winners of the playoffs will walk away with R1-million and the runners-up will pocket R600 000. For the latest sports news from Sunday World, click here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here